The Bottom Line
Immediate, measurable effects. Across all evaluations, firefighters showed meaningful reductions in stress, tension, and pain within a single session.
Firefighters valued it. 90100% would recommend or use again. Benefits persisted up to 3 days for most participants.
Works during operations. Used between calls during routine shifts and active disaster responsenot off-duty or post-incident.
Study Context

The formal evaluations (Woodmere, Albuquerque) were single-arm field studiesparticipants used Shiftwave and reported how they felt before and after. This design captures real-world signal but doesn't compare to control conditions. The LA Fires data is preliminary and collected under disaster conditions, which differ meaningfully from routine operations.
